Professor Ninian Peckitt, 63, claimed he was attempting to reduce the fracture when he hit the patient up to ten times while a colleague held his head .
Professor Peckitt struck the patient ten times as he was under anesthetic .
The patient, known as Patient A, had come to Ipswich Hospital in February 2012 after an industrial accident and was operated on by Prof Peckitt .
Medical Practitioners Tribunal Service (MPTS) found that his fitness to practice was impaired .